Articles.Content:
Those three were the latest additions/updates to my gamedata.

KSP crashed with as of now no discernible reason.

Logs:

https://www.dropbox.com/sh/opfoo68t774ftv0/91sspAlDNg
Could it be you are running out of RAM?
Shouldn't be, was below the maximum even before I installed rbray89's Active Texture Compression Mod.

[ERR 18:48:07.853] Exception when loading E:\Spiele\Kerbal Space Program 22.0\GameData\CrewManifest\Plugins\CrewManifest.dll: System.Reflection.ReflectionTypeLoadException: The classes in the module cannot be loaded.
  at (wrapper managed-to-native) System.Reflection.Assembly:GetTypes (bool)
  at System.Reflection.Assembly.GetTypes () [0x00000] in <filename unknown>:0 
  at AssemblyLoader.LoadAssembly (System.Reflection.Assembly assembly, System.String filePath, System.String url) [0x00000] in <filename unknown>:0 

Additional information about this exception:

 System.TypeLoadException: Could not load type 'CrewManifest.ManifestBehaviour' from assembly 'CrewManifest, Version=0.5.6.0, Culture=neutral, PublicKeyToken=null'.

And then later:

[ERR 18:50:21.515] Cannot find a Module of typename 'CrewManifestModule'
[EXC 18:50:21.519] NullReferenceException: Object reference not set to an instance of an object
[EXC 18:50:21.523] NullReferenceException: Object reference not set to an instance of an object

I'm guessing it's CrewManifest since you just installed it. But RemoteTech was also throwing out a lot of errors.

I deleted crew manifest and removed the texture compression mod - as it is intergrated into Texture Replacer now.

No crash, but I only played once since.
I had noticed a few exceptions from Texture Replacer too, if it was that and it got updated, it might have fixed itself.

It could be texture replacer. The other day I got rid of universe replacer and rbray's compression plugin. Seeing is how TR replaces them. It didn't work.. crashed my game. Deleted it.. reinstalled UR and rbray's compressor along with FASA. And that worked. I meant to post something in the TR thread about this. Idk if its something I'm doing wrong, but what your describing here is very similar to my experience after i tried TR. Game went from working.. to not.

Edited December 14, 2013 by Motokid600
